- Directory traversal / arbitrary file read; original/14_static.py:134 + original/14_static.py:152 – _secure_path only   
    rejects .., ., empty segments, path separators, and NUL bytes, so a segment like C: passes. On Windows this makes      
    _secure_path return C:/…; when join(self.norm_docroot, path) runs, the drive-qualified path is treated as absolute,    
    escaping the static root. A request for /C:/windows/system32/... would therefore serve files outside the intended      
    directory.
